.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Version 1.1" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple Unix command-line interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a Unix command-line interpreter designed to mimic the behavior of /bin/sh. It supports the execution of commands, both interactively and non-interactively, and includes built-in commands such as exit and env.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.TP
./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) ls -l
($) env
($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.TP
echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The Simple Shell includes the following built-in commands:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell immediately. Does not accept any arguments.

.TP
.B env
Displays the current environment variables.

.SH OPTIONS
The Simple Shell does not currently support any command-line options.

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
The Simple Shell uses the following environment variables:
.TP
.B PATH
Specifies the directories to search for executable commands. If PATH is not set, only absolute or relative paths can be executed.

.TP
.B PATH1
An alternative to PATH, used when PATH is unset.

.SH SCRIPT SUPPORT
The Simple Shell can execute scripts such as the hbtn_ls script:
.TP
.B /home/student_jail/student_repo/hbtn_ls
This is a custom script that runs the ls command.

